SUMMARY:Re-scheduled Lake Sonoma Hike
DESCRIPTION:Go Wild Hikers\nWildflowers are early this year\, and I have a
 lready seen some Orchids. Join me in search of early wildflowers at Lake S
 onoma. We'll hike through a magical madrone forest\, take in beautiful exp
 ansive views of the Mayacamas Mountain range as well as the Dry Creek and 
 Warm Springs arms of Lake Sonoma. We will visit some of the largest manzan
 ita and madrone trees I've seen. Best for individuals and dogs with at lea
 st a moderate level of fitness.\n\n**Where We Meet/Important Directions**\
 nLittle Flat Parking (A large gravel parking lot)\nFrom Hwy 101 take Dry C
 reek Road west towards Lake Sonoma. Go up the hill and across the bridge o
 ver the lake. Pay Attention\, it's the first right turn into "Little Flat"
  parking lot.\nGive yourself plenty of time to arrive. It's often farther 
 than you think.\n\n**Group Hike #336**\nDry Creek\, No Name\, North Slope 
 and Bummer trails - a loop hike\nLength - +/-5 miles/8 kilometers\nElevati
 on change - +/-900 feet/274 meters\nDifficulty - 7+ out of 10 some short s
 teep rocky sections\nMust be sure footed (confident and competent)!\nExpos
 ures - +/-30 % sun/70% shade - creek crossings\, rocky\, muddy\, poison oa
 k\, ticks/insects.\nBring plenty of water. At least 68 oz./2 liters!\nDogs
  - Yes\, must be healthy\, well behaved and on a leash.\nFacilities at tra
 il head - None - Port O Potti about 1.5 miles in.\nCost - $5 cash\nParking
  -$7-day pass can be purchased on-site using a credit card through the Rec
 reation.gov mobile app. Once on-site\, follow the posted Scan & Pay instru
 ctions. You will need to download the free Recreation.gov mobile app prior
  to your arrival as some remote areas have limited or no cellular service.
  For more information about paying on-site\, click here: [How Do I Use a S
 can & Pay QR Code to Purchase an Activity Pass?](https://recreationonestop
 test.servicenowservices.com/external?id=kb_article&sys_id=2011ea4a1b84bcd0
 76c1dbdbe54bcb1d)\nRemember to wear appropriate hiking shoes\, bring plent
 y of water for your dog too\, a hat\, snack\, layered clothing.\nPlease Do
  Not Use Any scented products the day of a group hike!\nOf course\, we wil
 l all look out for each other but ultimately\, hikers are responsible for 
 their own safety and well-being during hikes.\n\n**After Hike Gathering?**
 \nQuail & Condor\nBakery and Café\n44 Mill St Unit J\nHealdsburg\, CA 954
 48\n[https://www.quailandcondor.com/](https://www.quailandcondor.com/)\n(7
 07) 473-8254\nOutstanding new location with plenty of parking and a beauti
 ful cafe. Behind the Parish Café at the roundabout.\n\n**When We Meet**\n
 Sunday March 22\, 2026\n9:00 am - 12:00 pm\nIf your plans change after you
  sign up even if you're on the waitlist\, please update your RSVP.\nDo Not
  Attend if you are sick\, running a fever\, were exposed to or have tested
  positive for Covid-19 or any other contagion!\nHike may be changed\, resc
 heduled or cancelled in case of excessive heat\, rain\, smoke/AQI\, illnes
 s\, zombie apocalypse etc... Check your email the night before for any pos
 sible changes.\n\n**Notice to New Hikers Only**\n**"When a New Hiker (neve
 r hiked with me before) doesn't show up (No Show) to their first hike with
  the group\, they will be removed (not banned) from the group immediately.
 "**
